    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Experimental technique used to analyze short-lived chemical intermediates created when molecules are split by an intense flash of light. Analysis by spectrophotometry follows during a second, less intense, flash. This technique is useful in the study of the mechanisms of fast chemical reactions.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
